In Genesis, God sends the Flood to rid the world of corrupt mankind. Only Noah, a righteous man, and his family are spared, along with a pair of each animal species.
His Ark was a perfect menagerie, a microcosm of Creation. In this work, which is almost an exact contemporary of Charles Darwinâ€™s "Origin of Species", the Neapolitan painter Filippo Palizzi emphasises the joy of the animals leaving the Ark rather than the horror of the cataclysmic event. Palizzi observed camels and bears in Moldavia, and studied animals at the Jardin des Plantes in Paris.

Exhibition #TheOriginsOfTheWorld until July 18, 2021.
